text.tspan: Brontorina has a dream. She wants to dance. But Brontorina is rather large — too large to fit in
Madame Lucille’s dance studio. Brontorina does not have the right shoes, and everyone knows you
can’t dance without the proper footwear. Still, Brontorina knows, deep in her heart, that she is meant
to be a ballerina. James Howe introduces a lovable dinosaur whose size is outmatched only by her
determination, and whose talent is outmatched only by her charm. Accompanied by Randy Cecil’s
beguiling illustrations, here is an irresistible story that proves that no problem is too big when the
heart and imagination know no bounds.
